Another person in Bauchi State has tested positive for coronavirus, making it three cases in the state. The Deputy Governor of Bauchi State, Sen. Baba Tela disclosed this on Tuesday, while addressing newsmen on the situation in the state. The Deputy, who doubles as the Chairman, Task Force Committee on COVID-19, said the individual is a 55- year- old man. DAILY POST reports that the state governor, Bala Mohammed, was first to be tested positive for the deadly disease. Details shortlyâ€¦